---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Best Shopify Email Apps for Event-Triggered Campaigns in 2026';
const description = 'Compare Shopify email apps for event-triggered campaigns by event quality, suppression, lifecycle use cases, pricing context, sources, and practical tradeoffs.';
const apps = [['Klaviyo','Stores with many Shopify event-driven journeys','Rich events, segments, and conditional flows','Event governance and collision prevention are essential','https://www.klaviyo.com/features/segmentation'],['Omnisend','Retail teams automating common event paths','Accessible email and SMS workflows','Event timing and channel frequency need QA','https://www.omnisend.com/features/marketing-automation/'],['Sequenzy','Lean teams with a few high-value triggers','Focused sequence operations','Validate custom event coverage','https://sequenzy.io/'],['Brevo','Event-triggered marketing beside transactional email','Broad messaging and contact options','More manual event modeling','https://www.brevo.com/features/marketing-automation/'],['Drip','DTC teams tying triggers to repeat purchase','Commerce automation and reporting','May exceed a small store’s needs','https://www.drip.com/features']];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}><main class="container page-stack"><p class="eyebrow">Shopify email apps</p><h1>{title}</h1><p class="lede">An event-triggered email is only as good as the event behind it. Product views, orders, delivery, returns, and preferences should each move the customer into a clear state with a priority and an exit condition.</p><p>We prioritize event reliability, suppression, flow ownership, and measurable next actions. Confirm current pricing and custom-event capabilities from official sources before building a large trigger library.</p><h2>Shortlist for event-triggered email</h2><table><thead><tr><th>App</th><th>Best fit</th><th>First trigger</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead><tbody>{apps.map(a=><tr><td>{a[0]}</td><td>{a[1]}</td><td>{a[0]==='Klaviyo'?'Lifecycle event map':a[0]==='Omnisend'?'Retail event automation':a[0]==='Sequenzy'?'Three core triggers':a[0]==='Brevo'?'Marketing/transactional split':'Repeat-purchase trigger'}</td><td>{a[3]}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table>{apps.map(a=><section><h2>{a[0]} for event-triggered campaigns</h2><p><strong>Best for:</strong> {a[1]}. {a[0]} is useful when each event has a clear definition, owner, priority, suppression rule, and testable outcome. More triggers can create worse customer experience if they overlap or fire on stale data.</p><p><strong>Why it stands out:</strong> {a[2]}. Start with welcome, post-purchase, cart recovery, and one retention trigger, then audit collisions and data quality. Report orders, margin, complaints, unsubscribes, service outcomes, and maintenance time rather than promising a fixed revenue lift.</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Pros</th><td>{a[2]}; supports a governed event test; can use Shopify events.</td></tr><tr><th>Cons</th><td>{a[3]}; contacts, sends, integrations, and channels affect cost.</td></tr><tr><th>Pricing context</th><td>Verify official plans for contacts, sends, seats, automation, custom events, analytics, and SMS.</td></tr><tr><th>Source</th><td><a href={a[4]} rel="nofollow">Official product information</a></td></tr></tbody></table></section>)}<h2>Decision guide</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Trigger priority</th><th>Start with</th><th>Reason</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Complex event-driven journeys</td><td>Klaviyo</td><td>Flexible event and flow logic.</td></tr><tr><td>Focused trigger sequences</td><td>Sequenzy</td><td>Simple operations.</td></tr><tr><td>Repeat-purchase triggers</td><td>Drip</td><td>Commerce retention orientation.</td></tr></tbody></table><p>See the <a href="/shopify-email">Shopify email overview</a>, <a href="/alternatives">alternatives library</a>, and <a href="/guides/flow-collision-prevention">flow-collision guide</a>.</p></main></BaseLayout>
